title: Updated NFL injury report for Ravens-Cardinals: Status for John Brown, Darren Fells, more
text:
The updated National Football League injury report for Monday night's game between the Baltimore Ravens and Arizona Cardinals, as provided by the league, was released on Saturday. Injuries of note 
Monday 
CARDINALS: OUT: TE Darren Fells (shoulder). QUESTIONABLE: WR John Brown (hamstring). PROBABLE: WR Larry Fitzgerald (not injury related), WR Brittan Golden (groin). RAVENS: OUT: WR Breshad Perriman (knee), TE Maxx Williams (knee, ankle). PROBABLE: WR Darren Waller (concussion). Complete injury report

PROBABLE: DE Chris Canty (calf), LB Elvis Dumervil (not injury related), LB Daryl Smith (not injury related), WR Darren Waller (concussion), G Marshal Yanda (ankle). PROBABLE: CB Justin Bethel (foot), WR Larry Fitzgerald (not injury related), WR Brittan Golden (groin), DT Cory Redding (shoulder), DT Frostee Rucker (foot), LB LaMarr Woodley (chest).
